WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.994 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:02.994 --> 00:00:13.490 align:middle line:90%


00:00:13.490 --> 00:00:16.340 align:middle line:84%
>> So how I got into this field
was I started out as a computer

00:00:16.340 --> 00:00:18.050 align:middle line:84%
engineer, moved
to Silicon Valley,

00:00:18.050 --> 00:00:19.490 align:middle line:90%
tried to start a company.

00:00:19.490 --> 00:00:22.370 align:middle line:84%
And immediately, I realized that
my timing, in a word, sucked.

00:00:22.370 --> 00:00:25.197 align:middle line:84%
The dot.com bubble
exploded within months

00:00:25.197 --> 00:00:26.030 align:middle line:90%
of me getting there.

00:00:26.030 --> 00:00:31.208 align:middle line:84%
And I and 14,000 other people
were laid off in April of 2001.

00:00:31.208 --> 00:00:32.750 align:middle line:84%
I was also trying
to start a company.

00:00:32.750 --> 00:00:33.980 align:middle line:90%
I lost all my money.

00:00:33.980 --> 00:00:37.250 align:middle line:84%
And at a certain point, the only
job I could get in the Valley

00:00:37.250 --> 00:00:41.090 align:middle line:84%
was essentially a job that
was dialing for dollars.

00:00:41.090 --> 00:00:44.870 align:middle line:84%
I would have to call up law
firms and sell them technology

00:00:44.870 --> 00:00:46.160 align:middle line:90%
to manage their firms.

00:00:46.160 --> 00:00:48.200 align:middle line:84%
And the economy was so
bad, companies were not

00:00:48.200 --> 00:00:49.470 align:middle line:90%
even paying a base salary.

00:00:49.470 --> 00:00:52.040 align:middle line:84%
So if you did not close a
sale, you did not get paid.

00:00:52.040 --> 00:00:56.780 align:middle line:84%
Now, in that state of
desperation, of pure misery,

00:00:56.780 --> 00:01:00.950 align:middle line:84%
I remember getting online
on 2002's version of Google

00:01:00.950 --> 00:01:02.450 align:middle line:90%
and searching for some hope.

00:01:02.450 --> 00:01:04.040 align:middle line:84%
Now, I can't remember
what I put in.

00:01:04.040 --> 00:01:06.170 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it was how
to succeed at work.

00:01:06.170 --> 00:01:09.540 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it was why does
life suck so bad?

00:01:09.540 --> 00:01:11.940 align:middle line:84%
But what I discovered
was meditation.

00:01:11.940 --> 00:01:14.130 align:middle line:84%
So I flew to LA, took my
first meditation class.

00:01:14.130 --> 00:01:16.190 align:middle line:84%
And when I came back to
work, interesting things

00:01:16.190 --> 00:01:17.240 align:middle line:90%
started happening.

00:01:17.240 --> 00:01:19.940 align:middle line:84%
Within one week, I
doubled my sales.

00:01:19.940 --> 00:01:23.300 align:middle line:84%
And as I continued diving more
into the application of this

00:01:23.300 --> 00:01:26.750 align:middle line:84%
what I now call transcendent
practices, which includes

00:01:26.750 --> 00:01:28.700 align:middle line:84%
things such as
positive statements,

00:01:28.700 --> 00:01:31.760 align:middle line:84%
creative visualization,
mindfulness--

00:01:31.760 --> 00:01:33.710 align:middle line:84%
as I started applying
this in my work,

00:01:33.710 --> 00:01:35.630 align:middle line:84%
I continued growing and
growing and growing.

00:01:35.630 --> 00:01:39.020 align:middle line:84%
Four months later, I had
been promoted three times,

00:01:39.020 --> 00:01:42.200 align:middle line:84%
was made director of sales, and
asked to run the company's New

00:01:42.200 --> 00:01:43.410 align:middle line:90%
York office.

00:01:43.410 --> 00:01:44.960 align:middle line:90%
And so I did that for 18 months.

00:01:44.960 --> 00:01:48.350 align:middle line:84%
And then I decided I wanted
to do more with my life.

00:01:48.350 --> 00:01:50.690 align:middle line:84%
And I thought,
well, Nelson Mandela

00:01:50.690 --> 00:01:54.620 align:middle line:84%
said, if you want to change
the world, change education.

00:01:54.620 --> 00:01:56.690 align:middle line:84%
And I asked myself,
why is it that all

00:01:56.690 --> 00:01:59.420 align:middle line:84%
of these incredible
practices that I had learned,

00:01:59.420 --> 00:02:02.690 align:middle line:84%
from mindfulness, to meditation,
to creative visualization,

00:02:02.690 --> 00:02:05.300 align:middle line:84%
why did I only learn
them in my 20s?

00:02:05.300 --> 00:02:06.889 align:middle line:84%
Why was this not
taught in schools?

00:02:06.889 --> 00:02:08.389 align:middle line:84%
And so I thought,
well, look, if I'm

00:02:08.389 --> 00:02:10.650 align:middle line:84%
going to tackle education
to change the world,

00:02:10.650 --> 00:02:12.560 align:middle line:90%
I want to teach meditation.

00:02:12.560 --> 00:02:14.150 align:middle line:84%
And that's how
mindvalley started.

