rules that were

00:03:45.820 --> 00:03:48.460 align:middle line:90%
infused into them as children.

00:03:48.460 --> 00:03:51.850 align:middle line:84%
True religion, true media, true
fathers, mothers, teachers,

00:03:51.850 --> 00:03:55.990 align:middle line:84%
preachers, they question, and
they create their own rules.

00:03:55.990 --> 00:03:59.980 align:middle line:84%
Hunter S. Thompson, the
American writer, in 1953,

00:03:59.980 --> 00:04:02.750 align:middle line:84%
was asked to write a
letter to a friend.

00:04:02.750 --> 00:04:04.150 align:middle line:84%
His friend was
asking for advice.

00:04:04.150 --> 00:04:06.692 align:middle line:84%
And I remember something really
beautiful in that letter that

00:04:06.692 --> 00:04:08.140 align:middle line:90%
has now become legendary.

00:04:08.140 --> 00:04:11.560 align:middle line:84%
Hunter says the big
danger with goal-setting

00:04:11.560 --> 00:04:13.510 align:middle line:84%
is that we aren't
setting our own goals,

00:04:13.510 --> 00:04:17.019 align:middle line:84%
