purpose understand this rule,

00:12:40.420 --> 00:12:43.720 align:middle line:84%
that there is no good
or no bad that happens

00:12:43.720 --> 00:12:44.590 align:middle line:90%
to you in the world.

00:12:44.590 --> 00:12:45.640 align:middle line:90%
Nothing is good.

00:12:45.640 --> 00:12:46.630 align:middle line:90%
Nothing is bad.

00:12:46.630 --> 00:12:48.760 align:middle line:90%
Everything is just so.

00:12:48.760 --> 00:12:50.560 align:middle line:84%
The only question you
want to ask yourself

00:12:50.560 --> 00:12:52.840 align:middle line:84%
is, am I aligned
with my purpose?

00:12:52.840 --> 00:12:55.160 align:middle line:84%
Is what I'm doing
true to my purpose?

00:12:55.160 --> 00:12:59.140 align:middle line:84%
Now, the thing is we
are not omnisentient.

00:12:59.140 --> 00:13:01.480 align:middle line:84%
We don't know if any
action we are taking

00:13:01.480 --> 00:13:03.490 align:middle line:90%
is always the right action.

00:13:03.490 --> 00:13:05.980 align:middle line:84%
But the point is,
we take it anyway,

00:13:05.980 --> 00:13:09.520 align:middle line:84%
trusting that if it isn't
the right action, it's fine.

00:13:09.520 --> 00:13:12.580 align:middle line:84%
It will teach us, or
through that failure,

00:13:12.580 --> 00:13:15.460 align:middle line:84%
we will learn something
that lets us correct,

00:13:15.460 --> 00:13:17.860 align:middle line:84%
and correct again,
and correct again.

00:13:17.860 --> 00:13:21.100 align:middle line:84%
So if this is your goal and
this is where you are right now,

00:13:21.100 --> 00:13:23.020 align:middle line:84%
people who are living
on purpose are not

00:13:23.020 --> 00:13:25.180 align:middle line:84%
looking to get there
in a straight line.

00:13:25.180 --> 00:13:27.090 align:middle line:84%
They know that they
may make a wrong bet.

00:13:27.090 --> 00:13:28.930 align:middle line:84%
They may start a
company, and it may fail.

00:13:28.930 --> 00:13:31.150 align:middle line:84%
They may marry someone, and
that may end in divorce.

00:13:31.150 --> 00:13:34.300 align:middle line:84%
But each of these are simply
micro corrections where

00:13:34.300 --> 00:13:35.680 align:middle line:90%
they are learning something.

00:13:35.680 --> 00:13:37.750 align:middle line:84%
And these corrections
still eventually get them

00:13:37.750 --> 00:13:38.560 align:middle line:90%
to the goal.

00:13:38.560 --> 00:13:41.893 align:middle line:84%
Now, Michael Beckwith
thought me a model

00:13:41.893 --> 00:13:43.060 align:middle line:90%
which is really interesting.

00:13:43.060 --> 00:13:45.070 align:middle line:84%
It's called kensho
versus satori.

00:13:45.070 --> 00:13:49.350 align:middle line:84%
When you're living life, moving
towards a particular purpose,

00:13:49.350 --> 00:13:52.000 align:middle line:84%
there are two very important
things to understand.

00:13:52.000 --> 00:13:55.960 align:middle line:84%
Life helps us grow,
and correct, and evolve

00:13:55.960 --> 00:13:59.710 align:middle line:84%
through kensho, which
is growth by pain,

00:13:59.710 --> 00:14:02.830 align:middle line:84%
or satori, which is
growth by insight.

00:14:02.830 --> 00:14:05.740 align:middle line:84%
Every now and then, you
will have a satori moment,

00:14:05.740 --> 00:14:08.440 align:middle line:84%
a sudden awakening, a eureka
moment, an insight that

00:14:08.440 --> 00:14:10.060 align:middle line:90%
helps you move forward.

00:14:10.060 --> 00:14:14.710 align:middle line:84%
But for most people, that isn't
really going to be as easy.

00:14:14.710 --> 00:14:16.520 align:middle line:90%
Most of us grow through kensho.

00:14:16.520 --> 00:14:18.670 align:middle line:90%
Kensho is growth from pain.

00:14:18.670 --> 00:14:20.350 align:middle line:84%
You fall sick and
end up hospitalized,

00:14:20.350 --> 00:14:23.890 align:middle line:84%
but you emerge with new-found
respect for your body

00:14:23.890 --> 00:14:25.810 align:middle line:84%
and making new
choices in how you're

00:14:25.810 --> 00:14:27.010 align:middle line:90%
going to treat your health.

00:14:27.010 --> 00:14:29.530 align:middle line:84%
You start a business,
and it fails.

00:14:29.530 --> 00:14:30.670 align:middle line:90%
And it's painful.

00:14:30.670 --> 00:14:32.440 align:middle line:84%
But that's kensho
because now you

00:14:32.440 --> 00:14:35.420 align:middle line:84%
know what not to do
in your next business.

00:14:35.420 --> 00:14:39.340 align:middle line:84%
A relationship dissolves, and
you experience heartbreak.

00:14:39.340 --> 00:14:41.140 align:middle line:84%
But that's kensho
because now you

00:14:41.140 --> 00:14:43.660 align:middle line:84%
know the man or woman you
need to evolve to create

00:14:43.660 --> 00:14:45.350 align:middle line:90%
even better relationships.

00:14:45.350 --> 00:14:49.150 align:middle line:84%
So when you see life as satori
moments, sudden awakenings,

00:14:49.150 --> 00:14:52.810 align:middle line:84%
and kensho, growth
through pain, fear

00:14:52.810 --> 00:14:55.990 align:middle line:84%
dissolves because you know that
even when something bad happens

00:14:55.990 --> 00:14:59.170 align:middle line:84%
to you, it's simply a
friendly universe giving you

00:14:59.170 --> 00:15:03.290 align:middle line:84%
a lesson or fine tuning
and tweaking your direction

00:15:03.290 --> 00:15:05.400 align:middle line:84%
so you can get to your
purpose even faster.

